    "body": "@zcbenz, this fails:\n\n``` js\nvar { app } = require('electron');\napp.commandLine.appendSwitch('js-flags', '--harmony-destructuring');\n```\n\nThe current hack to fix it is to create two files...\n\n``` js\nvar app = require('electron').app;\napp.commandLine.appendSwitch('js-flags', '--harmony-destructuring');\n\nrequire('./real-main.js');\n```\n\nFurthermore, Electron already has helpers that stem from `package.json`, such as finding the `main` script, setting the app name, app version, desktop name, and more.\n"
  },
